You can choose longer or shorter segments of the coast to take to integrate your own activity level into the journey. Generally, participants take three hours on land to do a 10-15km relaxed segment that flows from reasonable to mod erate pace. Conveniently, our routes flow by local food producers or restaurants which means that there is an opportunity to incorporate delicious stops along the way. There is a good support system and a lot of spontaneous works on the way so even with complete beginners in hiking, kayaking can grow to be relatively easy operation.

There are different options of distances or we can modify them depending on your skills and comfort level. We develop the right distance and combination of other activities to ensure that the trip is at the right pace for you.

During the trip, you will always be accompanied by assistance kayak or bike team members

Travel dates are established a six months before each tour. The specific dates of the tours mainly depend on the availability of tour participants and available service team members. We always try to pick our startup days to line up with a full moon month, in line with Lithuanian and Latvian customs that make full moon nights a harmonious time for festivals, honoring ancestors, and raising toasts.
